## 10. Open Questions / Clarifications Needed

The following decisions MUST be resolved before task breakdown (`/speckit-tasks-phase-v`):

| # | Question | Options | Impact |
|---|---------|---------|--------|
| OQ-01 | **WebSocket scaling strategy** for multi-replica WebSocket Service | (a) Sticky sessions via Ingress; (b) Redis pub/sub adapter | If (b), Redis must be added to constitution (amendment required) |
| OQ-02 | **Notification delivery mechanism** for reminders | (a) Console log only (hackathon); (b) Email via SendGrid; (c) Browser push | Notification Service implementation scope depends on this |
| OQ-03 | **Image registry** for CI/CD | (a) GitHub Container Registry (ghcr.io); (b) Docker Hub; (c) OCI Container Registry | GitHub Actions authentication strategy differs |
| OQ-04 | **OKE image pull** for ARM64 | (a) Multi-arch buildx in CI (recommended); (b) separate ARM-only builds | Affects Dockerfile strategy and CI matrix |
| OQ-05 | **Frontend auth integration** | (a) Better Auth (already in codebase); (b) Extend existing auth | Must confirm Better Auth is already deployed before Phase V begins |
| OQ-06 | **speckit.specify** | Does a speckit.specify file exist at repo root? | If not, run `/speckit-specify-phase-v` before tasks |

